extendedInfo.description: Match Me is simple memory card brain game where you match up pairs. It is a fun memory and picture match game for kids, big and small. At the beginning of Match Me game all cards are laid face down. Two cards (pair) are flipped face up over each turn. If pair of those two cards are the same then they left open, otherwise they are turned face down again.The object of the Match Me game is to match up all pairs of cards in as little moves as possible. When cards are turned over, it is important to remember where they are.Features:1.	Multiple Themes2.	3 Level of difficulty3. reviews.title: Lost me with Jesus ads
reviews.comment: Don\'t like to be bible bashed. Especially inappropriate for small children. Uninstalled. And p.s. who is this aimed at? Way too difficult...
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Far too many pictures!
reviews.comment: This game appeared in the search results for pre-school games.  Someone tell me how a pre-schooler would have patience to play it with soooooo many pics to match in one game???? Wasn\'t even on my phone for 2 mins before uninstalling!
reviews.author: Fifi M

reviews.title: A Little too hard for the small ones
reviews.comment: There\'s just too many matches; it is overwhelming for my 4 yr old. But the pictures were a hit as well as the match subjects.  Just too much.  Also this is not ideal for tablet users.  A landscape option would be a great improvement.
reviews.author: A Google User
